{"word":"προστρέπω","slug":"προστρέπω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προστρέπω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to turn towards a god, to approach with prayer, supplicate</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to entreat</i> one to do, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> rei et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to pray that</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to approach</i> (as an enemy), <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}